summary:
I settled down for good in the Netherlands in July 2009 and in December I started working at Mexx as customer service representative. I worked there 6 months (replaced a woman in maternity leave).  

Immediately after, I worked 3 years as sales support for different countries at 3form. I really enjoyed my time there. I was part of a very international team and the customized products were beautiful and special (eco-friendly materials and architectural hardware solutions for the Architecture + Design industry). After 3 years I was ready for new challenges and accepted a job offer at Eichholtz.

I'm now still working at Eichholtz as sales representative for French speaking countries and Africa.
The products (luxurious furniture, lighting and accessories), the work place (spacious and modern), a great team (good atmosphere) and my clients (French and African) makes my work interesting, challenging and enjoyable.

Specialisation in : international business
-languages: French (mother tongue), English, Dutch
